ined by a competition between the\ngravity and the curvature of magnetic field lines. The eruption of the polar\ncrown cavity as a solid body can be decomposed into two phases: a slow rise at\na speed of 0.6 km/s, and an acceleration phase at a mean speed of 25 km/s.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 Jul 2011 14:37:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
